The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) has prohibited any airport official, who has neither undergone the mandatory airside drivers training, nor certified appropriately to drive on the airsides of the nation’s airports. According to the statement sent to The AmehNews and endorsed by Henrietta Yakubu (Mrs.) General Manager, Corporate Affairs saying FAAN is re-emphasising this policy to ensure operational safety, following a recently averted airside incident involving a Customs official, at the Murtala Muhammed Airport, Lagos.  READ ALSO THIS: FAAN Refutes Insecurity Looms As Okada Riders Take Over Lagos Airport Story With this directive, all airline officials, Security agencies, ground handling companies, and other stakeholders are hereby put on notice to ensure that their officials, that have airside related roles, and will need to drive, are sent to FAAN’S training department to undergo this mandatory training before been assigned to duty. The Authority will no longer take lightly any act of violation of this directive, in the interest of safety. FAAN….. Committed to her core values of Safety, Security and Comfort.